// Same filename as tests/lib/transitive_dup2/helper.ptt but a
// different module — exercises Codex's round-2 P1-11 finding
// where two transitive `use helper`s from sibling dirs were
// collapsed into one load by the raw-text dedupe.
val_one() int { give 1 }

// Codex round 3: `answer` here and `answer` in the sibling
// transitive_dup2/helper.ptt both define a free function with
// the same name. Pre-fix, both got emitted as `_h_answer` (the
// alias text) and the assembler rejected the second definition.
// Post-fix, each is emitted under the resolved-path canonical
// alias and they coexist.
answer() int { give 11 }
